Safehands is a family oriented health management app designed to help caretakers manage medications for their dependents. The primary goal of the app is to provide easy access to current medications of a given dependent to medical professionals, remind dependants to take their medications, and show other dependents and caretakers within a family unit which dependents have taken their medications.


The primary audience for this app is meant for caretakers and dependents. Caretakers are individuals who are taking care of a dependent, often in the form of a parent or guardian. Dependents are individuals who rely on a caretaker for assistance with daily tasks, such as children or elderly individuals. In some cases, Caretakers can also be dependents, such as an independent child who lives on their own.


Key features include:
Family unit creation
Composed of caretakers and dependents
Medication tracking and display
Reminders for dependents to take medications
Visualization of what medications have or have not been taken, for all individuals in a family unit to see
A database of common medications, and the option to enter your own if unavailable.


Getting started:
Register and create an account to use with the app, so that you can create your family unit, add fellow caretakers and dependents, and start managing your medication better.
